verses.verse: The <S%H3068>LORD<s%> <S%H4427>reigns,<s%> he is <S%H3847>clothed<s%> with <S%H1348>majesty;<s%> the <S%H3068>LORD<s%> is <S%H3847>clothed<s%> with <S%H5797>strength,<s%> with which he has <S%H247>girded<s%> himself: the <S%H8398>world<s%> <S%H389>also<s%> is <S%H3559>established,<s%> that it <S%H1077>cannot<s%> be <S%H4131>moved.<s%>
Your <S%H3678>throne<s%> is <S%H3559>established<s%> of <S%H227>old:<s%> you are from <S%H5769>everlasting.<s%>

The <S%H5104>floods<s%> have <S%H5375>lifted<s%> up, O <S%H3068>LORD,<s%> the <S%H5104>floods<s%> have <S%H5375>lifted<s%> up their <S%H6963>voice;<s%> the <S%H5104>floods<s%> <S%H5375>lift<s%> up their <S%H1796>waves.<s%>

The <S%H3068>LORD<s%> on <S%H4791>high<s%> is <S%H117>mightier<s%> than the <S%H6963>noise<s%> of <S%H7227>many<s%> <S%H4325>waters,<s%> yes, than the <S%H117>mighty<s%> <S%H4867>waves<s%> of the <S%H3220>sea.<s%>
